<div id='gazette_story'>
    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>THE NEW COOKIE CRISP FACTORY HAS ITS OWN COOKIE CAPER!</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20100708.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, July  8, 2010</b> &mdash;
    While we were very excited to announce the opening of the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/ckcfactory/">Cookie Crisp Cereal Factory</a>, we were also advised about some kooky happenings taking place inside. Yep, Chip the Wolf is at it again and your help is needed to get him out of there so the factory can get back to business as usual: <i>making a very delicious breakfast cereal!</i> Each room that Chip tampered with has turned into a <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/ckcfactory/">mini-game</a> that you can play to help save the factory, and get you awesome new items! <br><br>Charles Chipper, the owner of Millsberry&#039;s Cookie Crisp factory, explains: &quot;During our very first tour, we got word that Chip the Wolf snuck in disguised as someone else. He was probably wearing a bobble-head disguise. His first trick was in the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/ckcfactory/">Packaging Room</a> where he opened boxes of cereal and kept turning the lights out! If you can help gather all of the cereal in the amount of time provided, you&#039;ll be rewarded with a delicious prize. Next he made it into the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/ckcfactory/">Research and Development Room</a>, and then the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/ckcfactory/">conveyor belt</a> in the factory! Think you got what it takes to stop Chip? Well this week you can try your skills in the Packaging Room. Then in the next two weeks, the other rooms will be open to challenge you vs. Chip.&quot;<br>
<br>
And when you <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/ckcfactory/">play</a> the first game in the Packaging Room, you could win one of 4 different prizes for that game. And then in a few weeks the other 2 rooms will be open for game-play as well, with a variety of prizes&mdash;a total of 12 different new prizes you could potentially win! Just come back to each room to play again and try your luck at all of the prizes.<br><br>One recent visitor gathered all the cereal in the Packaging Room in time and was awarded a Cookie Crisp Cereal Tree! This lucky resident comments: &quot;It looked good enough to eat! I&#039;m going to play again just to see if I can get another.&quot;<br><br>Charles Chipper finds it funny that his name is so similar to that of the villain&mdash;<i>Chip the Wolf!</i> <br><br>Charles tells us, &quot;You know that Chip is short for Charles. I don&#039;t think my parents knew that, so growing up was definitely interesting. Imagine being called Chip Chipper? Looks like the wolf and I have a few things in common. But let&#039;s just get him out of town!&quot;<br><br>You heard Charles: <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/ckcfactory/">get Chip out</a>!<br>
    </div>

